### Step 7: Ephemeral heuristic

After the FYI section, identify emails that match ALL of:
- Priority is 🟢 (FYI)
- Sender is `noreply@github.com`, `noreply@linear.app`, or `noreply@*.sentry.io`
- Subject contains any of: "merged", "closed", "passed", "succeeded", "completed", "approved"

Display suggested trash targets:

```
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
💡 Suggested for trash (ephemeral notifications):
   10, 11, 12 — CI passed, PR merged, issue closed
   Type "trash 10,11,12" to clean up
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
```

### Step 8: Interactive actions

Present the action prompt:

```
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
📌 Actions
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Mark as read: Enter item numbers (e.g., "1,3,5" or "all" or "green")
Trash ephemeral: Enter "trash 10,11,12" to move FYI notifications to trash
Done: Enter "done" to finish

>
```

**Parse input and process:**

| Input | Action |
|-------|--------|
| `1,3,5` | Mark those numbered items as read |
| `all` | Mark all items as read |
| `green` | Mark all 🟢 items as read |
| `trash 10,11,12` | Move those items to trash |
| `done` | Exit |

**Before executing any action, confirm:**

For mark-as-read:
```
Mark 3 items as read? [Y/n]
```

For trash:
```
Move 3 items to trash? [Y/n]
```

If confirmed (Y or Enter), execute:

Mark as read via:
```bash
gws gmail messages modify --params '{"id": "MSG_ID", "removeLabelIds": ["UNREAD"]}'
```

Move to trash via:
```bash
gws gmail messages trash --params '{"id": "MSG_ID"}'
```

**Do NOT use `messages delete` — only `messages trash`.**

Show result after each action:
```
✅ Marked 3 items as read
```
or
```
🗑️ Trashed 3 ephemeral notifications
```

Re-show the action prompt after each action. Loop until user types "done".

## Edge Cases

| Situation | Behavior |
|-----------|----------|
| Empty inbox | "📭 No unread emails. Inbox zero!" — exit cleanly |
| gws auth failure | "❌ Gmail not accessible. Run `gws auth login` to re-authenticate." — exit |
| MCP call fails | "⚠️ [Service] enrichment unavailable — showing raw link" — continue |
| More than 30 unread | Show total count, process newest 30 |
| Slack email | Display with raw link, skip enrichment silently |

## Safety Rules

- **Never** send, reply to, forward, or draft any emails
- **Never** permanently delete emails (`messages delete`) — only `messages trash`
- **Never** create or update issues in GitHub, Sentry, or Linear (read-only)
- **Never** write email content to disk files
- **Never** display more than 80 chars of email body/snippet

